We recommended that Management:

Create a GSO to have a department assigned in the custody, safekeeping and issuances of supplies and PPEs of the LGU; 

Create an Inventory Committee who shall be responsible in the conduct of physical inventory of all PPE of the LGU including local road networks, indicating the total amount of each category of the PPE account to be reported in the RPCPPE and RPCLRN to be reconciled with the accounting records to determine any discrepancy;

Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to maintain complete Property Cards and the Municipal Accountant to keep PPE/Real Property Ledger Cards and ensure that their records are updated and reconciled;



      Require the Municipal Treasurer to maintain a local road inventory and road map and to periodically render RLRN, and furnish copies to the concerned offices; and

      Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

We recommended that Management instruct the BAC to:

Require the BAC Secretariat to:

Post the procurement opportunity in the PhilGEPS website, the website of the Procuring Entity concerned and at any conspicuous place in the premises of the Procuring Entity for a period of at least three calendar days;

Post the NOA, Contract and NTP in the PhilGEPS website, the website of the Procuring Entity concerned, if available, and at any conspicuous place reserved for this purpose in the premises of the Procuring Entity within ten days from issuance thereof for contracts with ABC of ₱50,000.00 above;

Prepare an Abstract of Quotations, setting forth the names of those who responded to the RFQ, their corresponding price quotations, and the lowest calculated quotation submitted; and

Ensure that the documentary requirements are provided by the bidders before awarding the contract.

We recommended that Management:

Instruct the BAC Chairman to ensure that all PPAs are procured in accordance with the APP of the LGU and to revise the APP should there be any changes to the proposed PPAs;

Require the BAC Secretary to post all NOA, contract, or PO in the website of the LGU or any conspicuous place in the premises of the PE and GPPB online portal for Emergency Procurement under the Bayanihan Act for information purposes;

We recommended that Management:
Create a General Services Office to have a department assigned in the custody, safekeeping and issuance of supplies and PPEs of the LGU;
Require the Inventory Committee to submit the result of inventory to the concerned offices to be reconciled with the accounting records for any discrepancy;
Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to:
Maintain complete Property Cards;
Maintain a local road inventory and road map and to periodically render RLRN, and furnish copies to the concerned offices;
Require the Municipal Accountant to keep PPE/Real Property Ledger Cards and ensure that their records are updated and reconciled; and
Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

We recommended that Management:

      Require the concerned municipal officials and employees to liquidate their outstanding cash advances. Failure to do so shall constitute a valid cause for withholding of their salaries;



      Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to ensure that cash advances are properly obligated;

      Instruct the Municipal Accountant to issue a certification that the previous cash advance of the accountable officer has been liquidated and accounted for in the books before granting a new cash advance;

     Require the Human Resource Management Officer (HRMO) to prepare the payroll voucher indicating the net payments for approval by the Local Chief Executive before the preparation of DV for the cash advance for payroll; and

      Instruct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to deduct the unliquidated cash advances of the concerned officials and employees from their salaries until fully liquidated.

We recommended that the Management:

Conduct complete inventory of the Local Road Network of the Municipality and require the Municipal Accountant, Municipal Engineer and Municipal Treasurer to reconcile the balances reflected in the Report of the Local Road Network with the accounting records;

Require the Municipal Treasurer to periodically render Report on Local Road Networks and furnish copies to the concerned offices. Also, Municipal Engineer’s Office provide the Municipal Accountant and the General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects in accordance with COA Circular No. 2015-008;

Instruct the Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant to maintain Local Road Network Property Card for each individual road network and Local Road Network Ledger Card, respectively; 

Require the Municipal Accountant to provide note disclosure on the Road Network System of the Municipality in the Notes to Financial Statements; and

Ensure coordination among LGU Offices to properly implement the accounting and reporting guidelines on the Local Road Asset Management System.

We recommended that the Management:

Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to locate and submit all the unrecorded disbursements with its respective supporting documents to the Accounting Office for proper recording in the books and to submit the same to the office of the Audit Team to avoid the issuance of Notice of Disallowance;

Require the Municipal Treasurer to coordinate with bank officials on the copies of credit memos to support the necessary adjustments to be made by the Municipal Accountant;

Require the Municipal Accountant to exert extra efforts to review the outstanding/stale checks and require the Municipal Treasurer to cancel the unclaimed stale check and forward to the Municipal Accountant the original DV and its supporting documents, for the preparation of JEV, following the procedures prescribed to ensure recording the transaction as Liability under the Accounts Payable account in the books of accounts;

Direct the Municipal Treasurer to send a written notice to payees of the existence of stale check at least one month before the check becomes stale; and

Ensure that book reconciling items are recorded immediately in the ensuing month, and respective banks are immediately informed of any bank errors for their immediate action.

We recommended that Management:
Require the municipal officials and employees with outstanding cash advances to liquidate their cash advances, otherwise, the Municipal Treasurer, impose administrative sanctions against them for any unjustifiable reasons due to failure to liquidate cash advances within the prescribed period, in accordance with PD No. 1445 and COA Circular No. 97-002; and
Instruct the employees/officials to observe the following in the granting/liquidation of cash advances:
Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to ensure that cash advances are properly obligated;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to issue certification that the previous cash advance was already liquidated before granting a new cash advance;
Require the Municipal Accountant to use Liquidation Report in liquidating cash advances instead of Disbursement Vouchers;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to require all municipal officials and employees to accomplish the Certificate of Travel Completed upon return; and
Require the Human Resource Management Officer to prepare the payroll voucher indicating the net payments for approval by the Local Chief Executive before the preparation of disbursement voucher for the cash advance for payroll.

We recommended that Management:
Instruct the BAC Chairman to ensure that all PPAs are procured in accordance with the APP of the LGU and to revise the APP should there be any changes to the proposed PPAs;
Require the BAC Secretary to post all NOA, contract, or PO in the website of the LGU or any conspicuous place in the premises of the PE and GPPB online portal for Emergency Procurement under the Bayanihan Act for information purposes;
Instruct the BAC member, with the assistance of Municipal Accountant, to submit the mandatory documentary requirements from the suppliers, distributors, manufacturers or contractors concerned; and
Require the Municipal Accountant to ensure that all documents are prepared and signed by proper signatories before effecting payment.
